<div align="left"><font color="#990000"> </font></div>







</div>







 
<div align="left">The anchor-shaped structure of Precambrian <i>Parvancorina
</i>(far left)<i> </i>is likely homologous with that of <i>Primicaris </i>(left
center) and the axis and ocular lobes of primitive trilobites such as the
Early Cambrian <i>Bigotinella </i>(right center). This may be a plesiomorphy of
primitive arachnomorphs, and may even be seen in the structure of basal arachnomorphs
such as <i>Marella </i>(far right),<i> </i>which lack pleural fields. The above discussions linking <span style="font-style: italic;">Parvancorina</span> to early arachnomorphs were formally published (see Lin et al 2006), establishing the basal clade Parvancorinomorpha.<br>







</div>







 
